

---



> You are a frontend developer working on a dark-themed productivity web app built with plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Below are the app's design tokens, base styles, and component patterns. Your job is to build a **dashboard widget row** containing two side-by-side widgets — a **date/time widget** and a **weather widget** (with two slides) — that visually integrates with this app's existing style. This is to replace the space being occupied by "Tomorrow Starts Tonight." remove the header and replace it with this new implementation.
>
> ---
>
> **Design tokens:**
> ```css
> :root {
>   color-scheme: dark;
>   --bg-base: #0a0a0c;
>   --bg-surface: #111118;
>   --bg-raised: #1a1a26;
>   --accent-primary: #7c6ef7;
>   --accent-warm: #f5a623;
>   --accent-cool: #3dd9c5;
>   --text-primary: #f0eff8;
>   --text-secondary: #7b7a96;
>   --text-faint: #3d3c52;
>   --border: rgba(124, 110, 247, 0.15);
>   --radius-md: 12px;
>   --radius-lg: 16px;
>   --shadow-soft: 0 18px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
> }
> ```
>
> **Component rules (from components.css):**
> - Cards use `.panel`: `background: var(--bg-surface)`, `border: 1px solid var(--border)`, `border-radius: var(--radius-lg)`, `box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft)`, `padding: 1rem`
> - Secondary text: `color: var(--text-secondary)`
> - Raised surfaces: `background: var(--bg-raised)`
> - All borders use `var(--border)` (purple-tinted at 15% opacity)
>
> **Typography (from base.css):**
> - Body font: `"DM Sans", sans-serif`
> - Heading font: `"Fraunces", serif`
> - Primary text: `var(--text-primary)` (`#f0eff8`)
>
> ---
>
> **Layout:**
>
> Render both widgets in a flex row with `gap: 12px`. Each widget is a `.panel` card with `flex: 1`. They should be equal width and sit side by side. On screens below 540px, stack them vertically.
>
> ```html
> <div class="widgets-row">
>   <!-- Widget 1: Date/Time -->
>   <!-- Widget 2: Weather -->
> </div>
> ```
> ```css
> .widgets-row {
>   display: flex;
>   gap: 12px;
>   flex-wrap: wrap;
> }
> .widgets-row .panel {
>   flex: 1;
>   min-width: 240px;
>   position: relative;
> }
> ```
>
> ---
>
> **Widget 1 — Date & Time:**
>
> A `.panel` card with a small muted label "Date" in the top-left and a `···` menu indicator in the top-right (purely decorative, `color: var(--text-faint)`).
>
> Content (left side):
> - Day name (e.g. "Tuesday") — `var(--text-secondary)`, `font-size: 1rem`
> - Full date (e.g. "April 14, 2026") — `"Fraunces"` serif, `var(--text-primary)`, `font-size: 1.4rem`, `font-weight: 500`
> - Week number (e.g. "Week 15") — `var(--text-faint)`, `font-size: 0.75rem`
> - Current time (e.g. "5:27 PM") — `var(--text-secondary)`, `font-size: 1rem`, live-updating every second via `setInterval`
>
> Content (right side) — absolutely positioned calendar dot grid:
> - A 7-column grid of small dots representing the current month
> - Each dot is `8px × 8px`, `border-radius: 50%`
> - **Past days:** filled, `background: var(--text-faint)`
> - **Today:** filled circle with `background: var(--accent-primary)` and a `2px solid var(--text-primary)` ring, sized `8px`
> - **Future days:** hollow, `border: 1.5px solid var(--text-faint)`, transparent background
> - **Empty cells** (before the 1st of the month): transparent, no border
> - Generate the dot grid dynamically in JS using the current date — determine the weekday offset of the 1st, total days in the month, and today's date number to assign the correct state to each dot
>
> All date/time values must be derived dynamically from `new Date()` in JavaScript — nothing hardcoded.
>
> ---
>
> **Widget 2 — Weather (two slides):**
>
> A `.panel` card with a small muted label "Weather" in the top-left and a `···` menu indicator in the top-right (`color: var(--text-faint)`). Contains two slides toggled by pagination dots.
>
> **Slide 1 — Current conditions:**
> - City name — `"Fraunces"` serif, `var(--text-primary)`, `font-size: 1.2rem`, `font-weight: 500`
> - Date line (e.g. "Tuesday, April 14") — `var(--text-secondary)`, `font-size: 0.75rem`
> - Weather emoji icon (`font-size: 2.2rem`) + large temperature (`var(--text-primary)`, `font-size: 1.8rem`) side by side
> - Three detail rows absolutely positioned top-right: Feels like, Rain (mm), Wind (m/s) — labels in `var(--text-secondary)`, values in `var(--text-primary)`, `font-size: 0.75rem`
> - Footer: "Forecast from MET.no" left · pagination dots center · "Updated at [time]" right — all `var(--text-faint)`, `font-size: 0.7rem`, separated by `border-top: 1px solid var(--border)`
>
> **Slide 2 — 4-day forecast:**
> - Four rows: Tomorrow, Thursday, Friday, Saturday
> - Each row in a 5-column grid: day name · emoji · `low° / bold high°` (low in `var(--text-secondary)`, high bold in `var(--text-primary)`) · rainfall mm · wind m/s
> - All values `font-size: 0.85rem`, `color: var(--text-secondary)` except high temp
> - Same footer as Slide 1, second pagination dot active
>
> **Pagination dots:** Two `6px` circles. Active dot: `var(--accent-primary)`. Inactive: `var(--text-faint)`. Clicking switches slide with `display` toggle.
>
