>
> **Live data — MET Norway API (api.met.no):**
>
> Fetch real weather data from the MET Norway Locationforecast API. It is **completely free, requires no API key, and allows commercial use** under a Creative Commons license.
>
> ```
> GET https://api.met.no/weatherapi/locationforecast/2.0/compact?lat={LAT}&lon={LON}
> ```
>
> ⚠️ You **must** set a custom `User-Agent` header — requests without it return `403 Forbidden`:
> ```js
> fetch(url, {
>   headers: { "User-Agent": "YourAppName/1.0 your@email.com" }
> })
> ```
>
> From `data.properties.timeseries`:
> - Current temp: `timeseries[0].data.instant.details.air_temperature`
> - Wind speed (used for "Feels like" label): `timeseries[0].data.instant.details.wind_speed`
> - Precipitation: `timeseries[0].data.next_1_hours.details.precipitation_amount`
> - Weather symbol: `timeseries[0].data.next_1_hours.summary.symbol_code`
> - For the 4-day forecast, filter one entry per future day closest to 12:00 noon and extract min/max temps across that day's entries, plus precipitation and wind
>
> Map `symbol_code` to emojis:
> ```js
> const symbolMap = {
>   clearsky_day: "☀️", fair_day: "🌤️", partlycloudy_day: "⛅",
>   cloudy: "☁️", rain: "🌧️", heavyrain: "⛈️", lightrain: "🌦️"
> };
> // default: "🌤️"
> ```
>
> The user will manually set its location in the settings to pass them to the MET API. Show a loading state while fetching.
>
